column23:
The Marketing team is exploring a concept of creating a sub-domain to facilitate Apple and Android Universal links in marketing materials.  The idea is that they'd create an app that would generate a catalog type and ID (eg. live + 1469 for Z100, or artist + 42064 for Audioslave) and pass that along with a collection tag to webapi.

Leads would have a collection populated with catalog attach items- all tagged with the same collection tag (eg. collections/marketing).

WebAPI would be passed that unique collection tag + catalog type + ID (eg. collections/marketing + artist + 42064) as inputs.

The collection lookup on WebAPI already obviously exists, but would need to accept the catalog type + ID values - (matching the catalog attach on the leads cards) and based on a match of all 3, return whatever data is needed via the Leads query of webapi.

Downstream, there's be a page that would render to users.  If there was a match via WebAPI, it'd use the data returned from that call... else, it would pass the same catalog type and ID number to AMP and get it from there.


Example card:
http://leads.radioedit.ihrint.com/#/edit/5bdc96cafef4767f0d17a9fd
