column83:
27/Nov/18 11:44 AM;MikeWoodruff@iheartmedia.com;Original Description from [~1114558]: 

{quote}Web is moving news.iheart.com/news/ over to www.iheart.com/news/ , using the webapi site -> timeline function to populate the data. Currently there is no way to get the Topic link/name out of graphql, please add this data (really anywhere is fine, summary, subscription or payload seem like reasonable places to me). For reference an image of one of the article tiles is attached, we're trying to populate the <a/> tag that's below the image and above the title.{quote}

We already include the collection/topic tag in the timeline service, just need to add the display name:

Stage query:

{code:java}
query NewsDirectory($site: SiteQuery!, $topic:String, $page: Int) {
        site(select: $site) {
          timeline(topic: $topic, page:$page) {
            pub_start
            payload {
              external_url
              is_sponsored
              feed_vendor
              canonical_url
            }
      	subscription{
          tags
						}
            summary {
              image
              title
              description
              author
            }
            slug
          }
        }
      }
{code}

Selected output:

{code:java}
"subscription": [
            {
              "tags": [
                "collections/iheartradio-music-news",
                "collections/trending-pop",
                "brands/DEFAULT- (2135)"
              ]
            },
{code}

For the two collections shown, the goal would be to provide the friendly names of "iHeartRadio Music News" and "Trending", respectively.  We'd want to retain the tag itself so that they can continue to generate the link to the topic page.

