https://710wor.iheart.com/content/2018-03-20-donald-trump-jr-cheated/ is failing AMP validation due to style in an H3 tag:

{code:java}
    <h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Aubrey O'Day</strong></h3>
{code}

The Content Tool allows users to apply style to header tags.  This causes the page to fail AMP validation as AMP disallows inline style.

I don't see what benefit centering an H2/H3/etc tag brings.  Should we prevent users from being able to do this?  Or set the ampEnabled flag to false?  Or something else?

